<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/4111/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 03 Jul 2014 15:04:13 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>How can I use i3lock with fingerprint-gui</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4111/how-can-i-use-i3lock-with-fingerprint-gui/</link><description>I really like i3lock and would like to unlock it with the fingerprint reader on my lenovo W530 (Upek 0x147e).
The fingerprint reader works flawlessly with fingerprint-gui.
To unlock the PC on login I added

    auth sufficient pam_fingerprint-gui.so

to /etc/pam.d/login.

I tried to add the same line to /etc/pam.d/i3lock to no avail.

</description><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jul 2014 15:04:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4111/how-can-i-use-i3lock-with-fingerprint-gui/</guid></item></channel></rss>